This project uses the UCI Adult Income dataset, which is publicly available through the UCI Machine Learning Repository. The dataset can be obtained manually by visiting the UCI Adult Dataset page at https://archive.ics.uci.edu/dataset/2/adult and downloading the accompanying data files, which include demographic and employment‑related attributes used to predict whether an individual earns more than $50K per year. If you choose to download the dataset manually, place all downloaded files—including the main data file and any accompanying metadata—inside the data/ directory of this project so that the folder structure remains organized and consistent.

However, manual download is not required. The project’s preprocessing code automatically retrieves the dataset using the ucimlrepo Python package, which downloads the Adult dataset directly from the UCI repository at runtime. If you rely on this automatic download, no files need to be placed in the data/ folder, and the dataset will be loaded programmatically without any additional steps. The data/ directory may remain empty unless you prefer to store a local copy of the dataset for reference or offline use.
